prime_award_base_transaction_description: VENEZUELA POLITICAL AND ECONOMIC CRISIS HAS DISPLACED OVER ONE MILLION VENEZUELANS TO COLOMBIA. COLOMBIAN RECEPTOR COMMUNITIES, ESPECIALLY LOCAL GOVERNMENTS, HAVE LIMITED RESOURCES AND CAPACITY TO PROVIDE BASIC SERVICES TO THE INCOMING POPULATIONS, WHICH INCLUDE VENEZUELANS AND RETURNING COLOMBIANS. THE INFLUX OF PEOPLE LEAVING VENEZUELA IS CONTRIBUTING TO INCREASED PUBLIC HEALTH CONCERNS, PARTICULARLY WITH REGARD TO THE SPREAD OF INFECTIOUS DISEASES; INCREASED XENOPHOBIA; INCREASED INVOLVEMENT IN ILLEGAL ACTIVITIES; AND TO GENERAL UNREST IN SOME OF THE MOST VULNERABLE AND CONFLICT PRONE AREAS OF THE COUNTRY. USAID/COLOMBIA IS TO PERFORM A CONFLICT ASSESSMENT OF THE COLOMBIA-VENEZUELA BORDER AND ITS CHANGING CONTEXT DUE TO THE RELATIONSHIP WITH THE INFLUX OF MIGRANTS INTO RECEIVING COMMUNITIES.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: D20182166 OFDA CONTROL NO. THE USG HAS BEEN SUPPORTING THE GOVERNMENT OF COLOMBIA GOC IN RESPONSE TO THE CRISIS FROM THE MASSIVE MIGRATION OF VENEZUELANS TO COLOMBIA. AS PART OF THE RESPONSE MANY OFFICIALS HAVE BEEN DEPLOYED TO SUPPORT THE USG OFFICIALS IN THE COUNTRY PROVIDE TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO THE GOC AND LIAISE WITH NGOS AND THE PRIVATE SECTOR IN ORDER TO PROVIDE A COMPREHENSIVE AND COORDINATED RESPONSE. THE CONSULTANT SHALL PRESENT A COST PROPOSAL FOR EACH SERVICE OR PROCUREMENT AS FOLLOWS  INTERPRETATION SERVICES FOR ONE DAY 8 HOURS MAXIMUM 19 DAYS  PRICE PER DAY 1500000.00 COP   INTERPRETATION SERVICES FOR HALF DAY 4 HOURS MAXIMUM 32 HALF DAYS PRICE PER DAY 900000.00 COP   INTERPRETATION SERVICES FOR EXTRA HOUR OVERTIME MAXIMUM 120 HOURS PRICE PER HOUR 240000.00 COP   EQUIPMENT RENTAL AT LEAST ONE TRANSMITTER AND FIVE RECEIVERS MAXIMUM 199 EQUIPMENT PRICE PER DAY 145000.00 COP   DOCUMENT TRANSLATION PRICE PER WORD MAXIMUM 180344 WORDS PRICE PER WORD 160.00 COP   TRAVEL EXPENSES AIR TICKETS GROUND TRANSPORTATION HOTEL PER DIEM, MEALS INCIDENTALS ETC. WILL BE APPROVED BY THE COR ON A CASE BY CASE BASIS. PLEASE SEE THE SOW ATTACHED.  MANY OF THE OFFICIALS DEPLOYED HAVE IDENTIFIED THE NEED OF BETTER COMMUNICATION AND UNDERSTANDING OF THE FACTS DURING MEETINGS WITH HOST GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS IN BOGOTA AND  IN OTHER CITIES THE FIELD E.G. CUCUTA, BUCARAMANGA RIOHACHA PASTO ETC. WITH IMPROVED COMMUNICATIONS, THE END RESULT WILL BE A BETTER AND MORE COMPLETE RESPONSE TO THE CRISIS.  USAID COLOMBIA AND OFDA PERSONNEL IN COLOMBIA REQUIRE THE SUPPORT OF TRANSLATION AND INTERPRETATION ENGLISH SPANISH AND SPANISH ENGLISH SERVICES DURING MEETINGS CONFERENCES AND OTHER ACTIVITIES IN BOGOTA AND IN THE FIELD.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF THE OFFICE OF ENVIRONMENT AT USAID/COLOMBIA IS LOOKING FOR TECHNICAL SUPPORT IN OVERSEEING PROGRAMS DEDICATED TO BIODIVERSITY CONSERVATION, CONSOLIDATING INFORMATION ON BIODIVERSITY TO CONTRIBUTE TO INTERNAL DISCUSSIONS AND DOCUMENTS AND REVIEWING PROPOSALS RECEIVED FOR NEW BIODIVERSITY CONSERVATION PROGRAMS. SERVICES REQUIRE TRAVELLING TO SITES, NO MORE THAN 6 NATIONAL TRIPS DURING THE YEAR, TO MONITOR AND EVALUATE PROGRESS OF PROGRAMS IN BIODIVERSITY CONSERVATION. DUE TO THE SPECIFICITY OF THE ACTIVITIES THIS PERSON WILL SUPERVISE, REPORT ON AND SUGGESTS IMPROVEMENTS OR SOLUTIONS TO DIFFICULTIES IN PROGRAM IMPLEMENTATION AND PROPOSALS REVIEWED. RESPONSABILITIES 1. MONITORS PROJECT IMPLEMENTATION UNDER GRANTS OR COOPERATIVE AGREEMENTS AND ENSURES ACTIVITIES ACHIEVE THEIR INTENDED RESULTS TO MEET THE BENCHMARK REQUIREMENTS IN ACCORDANCE WITH USAID REGULATIONS. 2. FIXES SITE VISITS, MEETINGS WITH IMPLEMENTING PARTNER S AND GOVERNMENT COUNTERPARTS WHEN NEEDED TO FOLLOW UP ON PROJECT ADMINISTRATION AND/OR IMPLEMENTATION. 3. REVIEWS AND COMMENTS ON PROJECT REPORTS SUBMITTED. 4. REPORTS ON THE STATUS OF PROJECT DEVELOPMENT AND DRAFTS PROGRESS REPORTS, HIGHLIGHTING ACCOMPLISHMENTS AS WELL AS PROBLEM AREAS IN NEED OF ATTENTION WITH RECOMMENDATIONS. 5. PARTICIPATES IN TECHNICAL DISCUSSIONS WITH THE USAID/COLOMBIA S OFFICE OF ENVIRONMENT AND CONTRIBUTES TO THE DEVELOPMENT OF TECHNICAL CONCEPT PAPERS. 6. PROVIDES TECHNICAL GUIDANCE AND EXPERTISE TO IMPLEMENTING PARTNERS AND WHENEVER POSSIBLE PROMOTES POSSIBLE SYNERGIES AMONG IMPLEMENTERS TO HELP ACHIEVE USAID OBJECTIVES. 7. HELPS ESTABLISH AND MAINTAIN STRATEGIC CONTACTS WITH GOC, OTHER DONORS, NON-GOVERNMENTAL ORGANIZATIONS (NGOS) AND ENVIRONMENTAL CONSERVATION ORGANIZATIONS TO EXCHANGE INFORMATION, COORDINATE EFFORTS AND AVOID DUPLICATING EFFORTS IN BIODIVERSITY CONSERVATION. 8. SUGGESTS WAYS TO LEVERAGE PRIVATE FUNDING TO COMPLEMENT USAID S EFFORTS TO PROMOTE BIODIVERSITY CONSERVATION IN COLOMBIA. 9. COLLECTS, ANALYZES, AND SYNTHESIZES RELEVANT INFORMATION FOR PROGRAM PLANNING AND OVERSEEING. 10. EVALUATES PROPOSALS AND SHARES THE CONCEPT OF EVALUATION WITHIN A TECHNICAL EVALUATION COMMITTEE. DELIVERABLES THE FOLLOWING ARE THE DELIVERABLES EXPECTED FROM THE PROCURED SERVICES: MONTHLY REPORTS FROM MEETINGS WITH PARTNERS ON TECHNICAL PROGRESS OF ACTIVITIES UNDER THE PROGRAMS FUNDED WITH BIODIVERSITY FUNDING. TRIP REPORTS FROM ON-SITE VISITS TO AREAS WHERE BIODIVERSITY PROGRAMS IMPLEMENT ACTIVITIES. TECHNICAL DOCUMENTS TO SUPPORT THE OFFICE OF ENVIRONMENT PLANNING AND PROGRAMMING OF BIODIVERSITY FUNDS. REPORTS ON FINDINGS AND CONCLUSIONS DERIVED FROM MEETINGS WITH DIFFERENT KEY STAKEHOLDERS RELATED TO THE AREAS AND TOPICS CURRENTLY AND IN THE FUTURE SUPPORTED BY THE OFFICE OF ENVIRONMENT WITH BIODIVERSITY FUNDING. REPORTS ON EVALUATION OF PROPOSALS FOLLOWING GUIDELINES FROM THE TECHNICAL EVALUATION COMMITTEE

prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF - THE PURPOSE OF THIS ACTIVITY IS TO SUPPORT THE GOVERNMENT OF COLOMBIA (GOC) IN REDUCING THE ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACTS OF SMALL SCALE GOLD MINING, WITH SPECIAL EMPHASIS ON ELIMINATING THE USE OF MERCURY, RECUPERATING DEGRADED AREAS LEFT BY GOLD MINING. THE SUCCESSFUL IMPLEMENTATION OF THE PROGRAM WILL RESULT IN IMPROVED, LAW-ABIDING MINING OPERATIONS IN THE TARGET GEOGRAPHIES. . THIS FIVE-YEAR PROJECT IS ESTIMATED AT APPROXIMATELY $20 MILLION AND INCLUDES AN ACTIVITY (SUB-AWARDS) FUND OF 65% OF THE TOTAL BUDGET. THE PROGRAM WILL BUILD ON THE RESULTS AND PROCESSES INITIATED UNDER THE MINING COMPONENT OF THE USAID/BIOREDD+ PROGRAM. STRONG PARTICIPATION OF THE PRIVATE SECTOR IS EXPECTED, AS WELL AS INVOLVEMENT OF THE RELEVANT COUNTERPARTS IN THE GOC AT LOCAL, REGIONAL AND NATIONAL LEVELS. ARTISANAL AND SMALL-SCALE MINERS (ASM) IN SELECTED MUNICIPALITIES OF ANTIOQUIA AND CHOCO ARE THE MAIN TARGET COMMUNITIES FOR THIS PROGRAM.
